Political Capital: Hungarian Guard increases state risk
According to the Risk Analysing Division of Political Capital, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, founded this August with the support of the "Force for Better Hungary", have raised Hungary's and region risks in several respects.
The institute's "Risk Warning Report" states, among other things: In the context of the activities of the Hungarian Guard, the highest political risk represents the "stifficultment of existing ethnic tensions between the gypsy and non-gypsy population in Hungary, which could even lead to violent ethnic conflicts in the short term."
The main reason for this is the strategy of the Hungarian Guard, which presumably aims at the provocation of such an dispute, said the research institute.
As reported, this is seen as a failure by those in political centers: "Persons of public life have left the discussion of the Roma question to representatives of radical political groups who have now built their political strategy on the contrast of Roma Hungary."
It is assumed that this would exacerbate the problem, make it impossible for sensible dialogue, favour clubs, and increase the likelihood of violent clashes.
The research instance also means that the activities of the Hungarian Guard have, not least thanks to the enormous attention from the domestic and foreign media, "the image of Hungary abroad has a considerable harm, especially as regards confidence in stability and democratic maturity."
We remember: since autumn 2006, the reorganization of radical and extremely right-wing groups in Hungary has been continuously on the upswing, so that since the summer of 2007 several organisations calling themselves "national self-defence association" have been founded.
"These groups have in common that they define themselves as a civilian organisation, while they openly brag to prepare their members for - sometimes armed - defense (disaster protection, national defence, order cutting), based on the unsuitability of the police, the army, or the state itself," it said.
And further: all this happened according to the method that attempts to camouflage various political aspirations based on the political and disenchantment of the population, as a bourgeois initiative.
The emphasis on the civil character and the form of the association therefore do not merely serve to circumvent legal hurdles that could appear in the course of the registration in court - it is also a political strategy.
As can be seen from the analysis, the activities of the Hungarian Guard are a risk-increasing factor for relations with neighbouring countries.
"In recent months, the Hungarian Guard has been cited as a potential source of danger in several neighboring states, some ultranationalist politicians of certain neighbouring countries see the emergence of the Hungarian Guard as confirming its own anti-Hungarian policy.
