Which insurance is best for me?
The car insurance, which covers a possible case of damage caused by the driver, includes a high cost, the amount of which depends on various factors, including age, gender, time of creation of the driving licence, marital status, type of car to be insured and use, etc.
Owning a car is just the beginning.
It is even more difficult to find the right car insurance than the right vehicle model.
First of all, it must be clear what we are dealing with here.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and an policyholder.
This agreement is set in writing by means of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the company receives the agreed insurance premium and in return is obliged to submit the corresponding severance amount in the event of a claim.
The insurance premium is the price of an insurance company composed of several factors, including. Age, gender, time of creation of the driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use.
The insurance companies set their prices according to the statistics, so that higher contributions are also due if there is a higher risk of accidents.
For this reason, both over 25 and women have to make fewer contributions, because statistics show that these groups have a lower accident rate thanks to their caution.
The same applies to married persons, since they, according to the statistical values and therefore also the reasons of the companies, they tend to accept fewer accidents such as single persons.
The benefits attached to the vehicle affects the frequency of driving and thus also the probability of an accident.
The more frequent the use, the more likely the damage.
When setting up the premium, insurance companies must take into account a whole range of points.
For this reason, the driver must also study the situation thoroughly in order to select exactly the car insurance that best suits his personal needs.
At this point, we now list the most important points that should be taken into account when selecting an insurance company in order to be able to make not only a performance, but also a price-oriented choice.
The under-age those under 25 people make numerous obstacles to the choice of a low-priced insurance, such as the low driving experience and the 'young' driving licence.
Even if it would be best for an ideal insurance cover to take out fully comprehensive insurance, there are still cheaper alternatives.
The careful drivers can choose a full cash match with excess, so that the benefits of a fully comprehensive insurance are covered but offered at a low price.
This type of contract implies that the customer has to pay a part of the amount incurred by the damage.
The amount will be determined before the contract is concluded and on the basis of the amount of the insurance premium. This is higher the lower the amount to be paid," explains Luis Noguera, Spanish's main representative at First Europa, a mediation company for online insurance.
Another option is the extended insurance that insures the customer against external accidental damage, but not against the damage caused by their own car.
In addition, this type of insurance would cover theft, fire and vehicle loss.
Here is an council.
If you are under 25 years of age, it is up to you to reduce the insurance costs, thus increasing your credit by trying to drive carefully and avoiding accidents.
A credit is a reduction in the basic rate at the relevant insurance company.
On the contrary, a penalty payment includes an increase in the tariff.
"The amount of credits and penalties depends on the company and its income.
If the company has had a year of profit, it can afford to increase the bonus payments," explains Noguera.
Once the 25-year mark is exceeded, it is easier for drivers to conclude a contract. The reason for this is the fact that the accident rate is decreasing with increasing driving experience.
It is therefore most useful to opt for fully comprehensive insurance with a deductible.
"Normally, young people cannot benefit from their previous experience, both in the event of an accident and at the time of driving," explains the Spanish head of the European company, and adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of practice after the 'fear of the beginner' has been taken.
Nevertheless, it is more advisable for a married customer who does not have children to take out full comprehensive insurance; of course, only if the financial situation of the corresponding person also allows it.
On the part of the insurers, couples with children are considered to be the customers with the lowest accident rate, and their contributions are also low.
In this case, full comprehensive insurance with excess (with an amount of 300 euros) would be the best option. In case you have received a high credit, an extended insurance policy is recommended, which only uses for the third year of the vehicle.
"They drive more relaxed overall and have greater purchasing power, which allows them to make a higher contribution payment," notes Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, it is advisable to take out full comprehensive insurance with excess (with an amount of 150 euros), or an extended insurance policy, which only uses with a sufficiently high credit.
Ultimately, it must be said that car insurance is something very important, not only because it protects the driver against possible accidental damage, but also because it has high costs, which require a thorough selection to be made that corresponds to our personal situation.
